I think we are at a point where this is not 100% what we wanted, but we can work with this. The “configureAsync” did not solve the issue for us unfortunately. For future readers, the switch we are using is the Adafruit Beam Break sensor plugged into the Forward Hard Limit Switch via the Data Port on a Spark Flex with Vortex Motor.

The code below results in the following behavior: If the right bumper button is pressed AND the beam is not broken, then the motor runs until the beam is broken and the motor stops quickly. No way to restart the motor unless we reconnect the beam by backing up the gamepiece. If the left bumper button is pressed AND the beam is not broken, then the motor runs without stopping when the beam is broken. Interestingly here, if the beam is broken while holding the left bumper button, we can restart the motor. If the back button is pressed, the motor runs in reverse. This is how we functionally reset the beam and then use the left bumper button to blow past the beam and score.

